==Football career== Fernando joined French [[Ligue 1]] side [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux]] in summer 2005, on loan from [[A.C. Siena]]. He made the move permanent a year later. He played an important role as Bordeaux finished runners-up for the 2005â06 [[Ligue 1]] season, and qualified for the 2006â07 [[UEFA Champions League]] season.
In the summer of 2007, despite several of his teammates leaving the club, such as [[Julien Faubert]], [[StÃ©phane Dalmat]], [[Rio Antonio Mavuba]], and [[VladimÃ­r Å micer]], he signed a new improved four-year contract with Bordeaux.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/competitions/uefacup/news/kind=1/newsid=565898.html|title=Fernando renews ties with Bordeaux|date=2007-07-31|work=UEFA.com}}</ref> He also played for the Brazilian national team when they won the [[2007 Copa America]].
On 16 June 2011, Fernando signed a three-year deal with Saudi Arabian club [[Al-Shabab Riyadh|Al-Shabab]] at the request of coach [[Michel Preud'homme]].
